wikipedia_page.main: James Maurice Quinton (12 May 1874 – 22 December 1922) was an English first-class cricketer, a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm fast.

response: Quinton's brother, James Quinton, also represented Hampshire in first-class cricket. Quinton played alongside James in two matches against Sussex and Yorkshire. In the report of the inquest into his brother's suicide in 1922, Quinton is identified as "Brigadier-General Francis Quinton".
